    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In archaeology, refers to deposit sites formed at the bottom of or along the shores of depressions in the earth that are filled with water, and that are smaller than an ocean or sea and ranging in size from just a few square meters to thousands of square kilometers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
